<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="317" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1436,222,354]" pageId="12" pageNumber="317">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,507,258,283]" pageId="12" pageNumber="317">Distribution and ecology.</emphasis>
Described from 
<collectingCountry box="[708,820,258,282]" name="Mongolia" pageId="12" pageNumber="317">Mongolia</collectingCountry>
, widely distributed in western and southern areas of Siberia. The species has been recorded all over Buryatia by us (
<figureCitation box="[867,936,294,318]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,250,1885,1908]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,700,1863]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[151,1436,700,1864]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. The sampling sites in Buryatia: 1 – 2 — Vitim Plateau (1 — Konda Basin, 2 — Eravna Basin), 3 – 5 — Selenga Low Plateau (3 — Zagansky Range, 4 — vicinities of Schuch'ye Lake, 5 — vicinities of Karasinoye Lake), 6 – 8 — Barguzinsky Range (6 — Ust' - Barguzin, 7 — vicinities of Barguzin, 8 — upper flow of Barguzin River), 9 — Khamar-Daban Range, 10 — Tunkinskiye Gol'tsy Range, 11 — vicinities of Ulan-Ude, 12 — estuary of Selenga River, 13 — vicinities of Khorinsk, 14 — vicinities of Unnokent'evka, 15 –– Turka." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/254496/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="317">
Fig. 
<number box="[920,936,294,318]" pageId="12" pageNumber="317" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
: loc. 
<number box="[998,1043,294,318]" pageId="12" pageNumber="317" value="1.3">1, 3</number>
, 
<number box="[1055,1184,294,318]" pageId="12" pageNumber="317" value="7.904999999999999" valueMax="10.11" valueMin="5.7">5, 7–10, 11</number>
), but is probably at its eastern limit. In damp mountains forests, more rarely in alpine sites.
</paragraph>
